<P>
WEISS DROPPED BECAUSE OF INJURY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Walt Weiss was dropped from the Oakland Athletics' World Series roster because 
of the strained ligaments in his left knee he suffered during the American 
League playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
"I probably needed three more weeks if I seriously thought about getting out 
there," Weiss said. "It's going to be tough to feel involved when I'm used to 
being out there every day." 
</P>
<P>
Infielder Mike Bordick replaces Weiss on the roster. Mike Gallego will start at 
shortstop and Willie Randolph will start at second, where he and Gallego have 
been platooned. 
</P>
