<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: ENCINITAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A San Dieguito High School teacher accused of molesting four teen-age girls 
pleaded not guilty Monday. 
</P>
<P>
George Dewey Warner III, 34, is charged with committing a lewd act with a 
minor, two counts of sexual battery on another girl and two misdemeanor counts 
of child molesting with two other girls. 
</P>
<P>
Warner, who had been free on $33,000 bail posted eight hours after his arrest 
Oct. 6, was allowed to remain free by Municipal Judge Michael Orfield. 
</P>
<P>
The judge ordered Warner not to contact the alleged victims or their families 
and not to associate with minors without the presence of an adult. 
</P>
<P>
Warner is on administrative leave from the school. 
</P>
<P>
"These crimes are alleged to have occurred outside the classroom," said Deputy 
Dist. Atty. John Williams, who declined to elaborate. 
</P>
<P>
The girls are between the ages of 15 and 17, and one of the charges states that 
the incident took place almost a year ago. 
</P>
<P>
A preliminary hearing was scheduled for Dec. 14. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
