<TEXT>
<P>
T-Bill Rates Nearly Unchanged: The Treasury sold $9.4 billion of new 
three-month bills at an average discount rate of 7.18%, down from 7.19% last 
week. 
</P>
<P>
Another $9.4 billion of new six-month bills was sold at an average discount 
rate of 7.22%, up from 7.21% last week. The new discount rates understate the 
actual return to investors -- 7.41% for three-month bills, with a $10,000 bill 
selling for $9,818.50, and 7.60% for a six-month bill selling for $9,635.00. 
The discount rate reflects the price discount received when government 
securities are purchased at less than face value. 
</P>
</TEXT>
