MORNING REPORT: MOVIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CLAUDIA PUIG, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sir Peter: Humorist and actor Peter Ustinov will be officially invested as a 
knight of Her Majesty Queen Elizabeth II today. The actor, who has been dubbed 
Sir Peter since the June announcement of his impending knighthood, also has a 
book due to be published in Britain this week, "The Old Man and Mr. Smith." 
