<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: POP/ROCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CLAUDIA PUIG, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
2 Live Crew Canceled Again: A Saturday performance of the group 2 Live Crew in 
Flint, Mich., has been canceled on the heels of recent cancellations in Detroit 
and Jackson, Mich. 
</P>
<P>
Flint's mayor sent a letter to theater management notifying them of the charges 
for additional city police protection during the concert. The theater manager 
indicated that this $5,200 charge would be passed on to the concert promoters 
and promoters declined altogether. The group is still scheduled to play in Los 
Angeles at the Palace on Nov. 8 and at the Celebrity Theater in Anaheim on Nov. 
9. CLAUDIA PUIG 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
