<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 7TH PERSON ARRESTED IN PARTY SHOOT-OUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A seventh person was arrested in connection with what detectives characterized 
as a racially motivated shoot-out at a Tarzana party that left four people 
injured, Los Angeles police said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Michael Anello, 19, of Encino was arrested Sunday on suspicion of attempted 
murder in the Friday night gunfight that erupted between a white supremacist 
gang and a black gang at a house party in the 4700 block of Hermano Drive, 
Detective Joe Diglio said. 
</P>
<P>
Anello, who was acting as a bouncer at the racially mixed party attended by 
about 200 people, allegedly pulled a gun and fired it during the confused 
shoot-out in the street outside the house, Diglio said. Four people were 
wounded in the cross-fire. 
</P>
<P>
According to police, a member of the white supremacist gang shouted "white 
power" and opened fire with a shotgun during the party. As party-goers 
scattered into the street, white gang members exchanged gunfire with black gang 
members, police said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
