<P>
RUTH ANN HODGES; FORMER GROCERY STORE OWNER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ruth Ann Hodges, who once owned a neighborhood market in North Hollywood, has 
died in a Glendale retirement home. She was 89. 
</P>
<P>
Mrs. Hodges died Friday of heart failure, said her son-in-law, Mark Forrest. 
</P>
<P>
Born Ruth Ann Reed on Sept. 4, 1901, in Dayton, Ohio, she came to California as 
a young woman and later settled in Sepulveda. From about 1970 to 1980, she and 
her husband owned and operated the Community Market in North Hollywood. 
</P>
<P>
She is survived by a grandson, William Huber of Encino; a granddaughter, 
Christine Conover of Glendale; and a great-granddaughter. Her husband, Frank 
Hodges, died in 1984. 
</P>
<P>
A memorial service is scheduled for 4 p.m. today at Pierce Brothers Valhalla 
Mortuary, 10621 Victory Blvd. in North Hollywood, which is handling 
arrangements. 
</P>
