<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Chris Pasles and Tom McQueeney 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KILLER HANDS: Four serial killers, including Randy Kraft and William Bonin from 
Orange County, spend their free hours on San Quentin's Death Row playing 
bridge, says the current Vanity Fair (E1). . . . Told of the card games, Deputy 
Dist. Atty. Bryan Brown, who prosecuted both Kraft and Bonin, was incredulous. 
"We introduced evidence that Kraft had a death list of more than 65 people and 
Bonin had confessed to at least another 22 people, and they're up there playing 
bridge?" Chris Pasles and Tom McQueeney 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
BRIDGE (GAME); KRAFT, RANDY STEVEN; BONIN, WILLIAM GEORGE; SERIAL MURDERS -- 
ORANGE COUNTY; SERIAL MURDERS -- LOS ANGELES COUNTY; PRISONERS -- CALIFORNIA 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
