<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: ORANGE; 
</P>
<P>
GROUND IS BROKEN FOR CHILD CARE CENTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Groundbreaking ceremonies for Rancho Santiago College's new Child Development 
Center were held Monday at the college's Orange campus. 
</P>
<P>
The new center will provide child-care service to students attending the Orange 
campus, which is at the corner of Chapman and Newport avenues. 
</P>
<P>
The center will also serve as a laboratory site for students in the college's 
Human Development Program. 
</P>
<P>
Officials participating in the groundbreaking ceremony included Orange Mayor 
Don E. Smith, Orange Unified School District President Jeff Holstein and Rancho 
Santiago College District Board President Vernon S. Evans. 
</P>
<P>
"The center is the next important step in the continuing development of Rancho 
Santiago's Orange campus," Evans said. "This . . . will give more local 
residents, those with children, an opportunity to attend classes at the Orange 
campus." 
</P>
<P>
Construction of the new facility will begin later this month. It is scheduled 
to open next August. 
</P>
</TEXT>
