<HEADLINE>
<P>
OFFERING RAISES $3.4 MILLION FOR PARKER CORP. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
COSTA MESA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Parker Automotive Corp. said Monday that it raised $3.4 million in a private 
offering to institutional investors that closed Oct. 9 -- bringing the total 
raised in a two-part offering that began in late August to $5.3 million. 
</P>
<P>
The company, which has reported signing numerous exclusive distributorship 
deals in the past year, said that it initially planned to raise only $2 million 
through the offerings but that demand for the unregistered common stock was 
much greater than anticipated. 
</P>
<P>
Cruttenden &amp; Co. of Newport Beach acted as adviser in both offerings. 
</P>
<P>
Company officials declined to identify any of the investors who bought stock in 
the two offerings. 
</P>
<P>
Parker Automotive manufactures and markets a cleaning system for internal 
combustion engine fuel systems. 
</P>
<P>
Michael Parker, chairman and chief executive, said proceeds will be used to 
finance continued expansion of the company. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
PARKER AUTOMOTIVE CORP; STOCK OFFERINGS 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA101690-0147 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 293324 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
October 16, 1990, Tuesday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Business; Part D; Page 7; Column 1; Financial Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
117 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Parker Automotive Corp.: The Costa Mesa manufacturer of engine cleaning 
products reported second-quarter earnings of $205,800, contrasted with a loss 
of $48,000 for the comparable quarter in 1989. 
</P>
<P>
Revenue for the quarter ended Aug. 31 more than doubled to $3.6 million from 
$1.3 million. For the six-month period, earnings totaled $1.5 million, 
contrasted with a loss of $833,300 for the year-earlier period. Revenue rose to 
$7.7 million from $1.6 million. The company said earnings in the second quarter 
were adversely affected by postponement of a shipment to Saudi Arabia due to 
the Iraqi invasion of Kuwait. The Saudi shipment will be reflected in the 
company's third quarter results. 
</P>
</TEXT>
