<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS: PRINTRONIX NET INCOME, SALES DROP IN SECOND FISCAL 
QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Printronix Inc., the Irvine manufacturer of computer printers, reported that 
net income fell to $201,000 for the second fiscal quarter, from $1.2 million 
for the corresponding quarter in 1989. 
</P>
<P>
Sales for the quarter ended Sept. 28 declined 13%, to $27.9 million from $31.9 
million. 
</P>
<P>
First-half net income nearly doubled, to $1.2 million from $630,000. Sales were 
down 6%, to $57.6 million from $61.1 million. 
</P>
<P>
Printronix said the lower sales levels reflect a persistent weakness in the 
North American market created by a general industry downturn and economic 
recession. 
</P>
