<TEXT>
<P>
Leaders of Central America's congresses and national assemblies meet in 
Panama's capital Thursday to review regional programs dealing with narcotics 
trafficking and environmental damage. 
</P>
<P>
The parliamentary presidents and vice presidents will also assess the 
opportunities for increased economic, political and cultural integration of the 
six Central American nations. 
</P>
