NATION; 
</P>
<P>
ANTI-GULF PROTESTERS SPILL OIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Half a dozen demonstrators opposed to U.S. military involvement in the Persian 
Gulf poured a quart of oil onto a patio in front of the American Petroleum 
Institute today to show support for a Marine who refused to be sent to Saudi 
Arabia. 
</P>
<P>
The protesters read a message from the 22-year-old Marine, Cpl. 
</P>
<P>
Jeffrey Paterson, who is confined to his base in Hawaii awaiting a 
court-martial. 
</P>
<P>
Paterson's message urged other Americans to join him in saying: "Hell, no, we 
won't go, we won't fight for Texaco." 
</P>
<P>
Two counter-demonstrators also showed up. 
</P>
<P>
David Almasi, who said he worked in a building next door, came to the lunchtime 
rally with a handmade sign asking: "Why did Jeff Paterson join the Marines? To 
surf? Or the free paycheck?" 
</P>
