SHORT TAKES; 
</P>
<P>
ACTOR BEGLEY BOOSTS RECYCLING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ed Begley Jr. says he has been into recycling since 1970 and recently refused a 
ride in an NBC limousine during a promotional tour for his new TV series, 
"Parenthood." 
</P>
<P>
Instead, Begley said in the November issue of Redbook, he rode his bike from 
his San Fernando Valley home to the Century City studio. 
</P>
<P>
"It's late. But it's not too late," said the former "St. Elsewhere" star, who 
is on the boards of seven environmental organizations and recycles everything 
from newspapers to metal products. 
</P>
<P>
"People have to realize that they can turn this around quicker than they think. 
How? By exercising their voting power and their purchasing power." 
</P>
</TEXT>
